<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{8}{\left({10}^{{{5}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.06</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{8}{\left({10}^{{{5}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{\left({10}^{{{5}{x}}}\right)}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{{5}{x}}}=-\frac{{4}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{8}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{8}}\right)}}}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx-{0.06}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

